1
00:00:14,133 --> 00:00:15,967
We can now get the result
of our appeal.

2
00:00:16,033 --> 00:00:17,600
I'm going to get released!

3
00:00:17,667 --> 00:00:19,333
This is good news!

4
00:00:19,400 --> 00:00:21,700
Eden will be happy to hear this.

5
00:00:21,767 --> 00:00:22,733
Help!

6
00:00:22,800 --> 00:00:23,733
Help!

7
00:00:23,800 --> 00:00:25,633
Someone's here!
Someone else is here!

8
00:00:25,700 --> 00:00:27,500
What are the chances
that my son is still alive?

9
00:00:27,567 --> 00:00:29,033
Everyone's on the move now, Sir.

10
00:00:29,100 --> 00:00:31,167
They're having a hard time
trying to pinpoint

11
00:00:31,233 --> 00:00:32,800
the exact location
where the plane crashed.

12
00:00:32,867 --> 00:00:34,533
Is there anyone else out there?

13
00:00:37,667 --> 00:00:38,933
Miss, hold on to me.

14
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:40,300
You're the guy from the campus.

15
00:00:40,367 --> 00:00:42,067
- By the way, I'm Red.
- Just call me Yenyen.

16
00:00:42,133 --> 00:00:43,900
I hope there are
other survivors.

17
00:00:43,967 --> 00:00:44,967
Never give up.

18
00:00:45,033 --> 00:00:46,000
- Let me make a call.
- I'll do it.

19
00:00:46,067 --> 00:00:47,000
- Let me make a call!
- Let me have it.

20
00:00:47,067 --> 00:00:48,700
Don't be stubborn!
Give it to me!

21
00:00:48,767 --> 00:00:51,133
- Let me do it! I'll do it!
- Let me make a call.

22
00:00:51,200 --> 00:00:52,600
Don't lose hope, okay?

23
00:00:52,667 --> 00:00:54,467
The mere fact
that we're alive and safe...

24
00:00:54,533 --> 00:00:57,200
Some rescuers might be
on their way here.

25
00:00:57,267 --> 00:00:59,900
How will they know
that we're here?

26
00:01:46,767 --> 00:01:49,533
Do you think the helicopter
will see this?

27
00:01:49,600 --> 00:01:50,833
I'm sure they'll know
there are survivors here

28
00:01:50,900 --> 00:01:53,267
if a helicopter passes by.

29
00:01:54,333 --> 00:01:56,400
I don't think this is enough.

30
00:01:56,467 --> 00:01:58,600
We need to make a fire.

31
00:01:58,667 --> 00:02:00,833
Miss Vinluan taught me how to
do it when we went camping.

32
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:03,200
They will know
that someone's out here

33
00:02:03,267 --> 00:02:05,067
when they see the smoke.

34
00:02:06,200 --> 00:02:09,667
It won't be easy,
but we have to do it.

35
00:02:09,733 --> 00:02:10,700
I'll help you.

36
00:02:17,933 --> 00:02:18,867
Why?

37
00:02:19,900 --> 00:02:20,867
- Look.
- What is it?

38
00:02:21,900 --> 00:02:22,833
I'll go there.

39
00:02:22,900 --> 00:02:23,900
No, let me do it.

40
00:02:23,967 --> 00:02:25,467
I'm a swimmer. I can do it.

41
00:04:02,267 --> 00:04:03,233
My son.

42
00:04:19,433 --> 00:04:20,667
Are you okay?

43
00:04:20,733 --> 00:04:21,700
I'm okay.

44
00:04:23,200 --> 00:04:24,833
Let's see what we have here.

45
00:04:24,900 --> 00:04:26,633
Open it.

46
00:04:26,700 --> 00:04:27,667
Wait.

47
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:36,167
Costume?

48
00:04:44,200 --> 00:04:45,600
Look at this.

49
00:04:45,667 --> 00:04:46,900
Abracadabra!

50
00:04:51,467 --> 00:04:53,833
I wonder if he can
still host parties.

51
00:04:53,900 --> 00:04:55,333
Whoever owns this.

52
00:04:57,600 --> 00:04:59,500
Can he still make
children happy?

53
00:05:01,733 --> 00:05:02,667
Don't be sad.

54
00:05:04,167 --> 00:05:05,267
I just remembered.

55
00:05:06,267 --> 00:05:09,000
We had a lot of co-passengers
on that plane.

56
00:05:09,067 --> 00:05:11,100
A lot of lives need to be saved.

57
00:05:13,833 --> 00:05:14,800
I know.

58
00:05:16,600 --> 00:05:18,433
We can use this one.

59
00:05:25,900 --> 00:05:27,100
What's in here?

60
00:05:30,067 --> 00:05:31,967
This one! We can use this too.

61
00:05:33,200 --> 00:05:34,500
It has batteries.
Don't waste it.

62
00:05:37,400 --> 00:05:39,333
Yes! Yes!

63
00:05:39,400 --> 00:05:41,133
We can use this for sure.

64
00:05:41,200 --> 00:05:42,167
Toiletries!

65
00:05:43,200 --> 00:05:46,233
Look, there's a shaving kit,
shampoo and soap.

66
00:05:46,300 --> 00:05:48,367
And most importantly...

67
00:05:48,433 --> 00:05:49,867
toothbrush and toothpaste.

68
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:52,533
It looks used, though.

69
00:05:52,600 --> 00:05:53,733
There's only one toothbrush.

70
00:05:53,800 --> 00:05:55,867
Do you want to share this
with me?

71
00:05:59,033 --> 00:06:01,633
Okay, you can use
the toothbrush.

72
00:06:01,700 --> 00:06:04,200
I'll just use my fingers
to brush my teeth.

73
00:06:04,267 --> 00:06:05,233
I'll do it now.

74
00:06:06,233 --> 00:06:07,267
What are you doing? Stop it.

75
00:06:07,367 --> 00:06:08,567
You're so childish.

76
00:06:12,333 --> 00:06:13,733
Gosh.

77
00:06:13,800 --> 00:06:14,933
You're so serious.

78
00:06:16,033 --> 00:06:17,900
Try to laugh a little.

79
00:06:17,967 --> 00:06:19,733
There's no reason for me
to laugh.

80
00:06:23,700 --> 00:06:25,133
Okay, fine. Really.

81
00:06:29,733 --> 00:06:32,767
Aren't you tired?

82
00:06:32,833 --> 00:06:33,933
Why?

83
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:37,667
Because you've been running
in my head.

84
00:06:37,733 --> 00:06:39,133
Stop it.

85
00:06:40,700 --> 00:06:41,767
What are you doing?

86
00:06:43,400 --> 00:06:45,800
Are you not aware
of our situation?

87
00:06:45,867 --> 00:06:47,167
Are you not worried?

88
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:50,000
Of course, I'm worried.

89
00:06:52,167 --> 00:06:54,400
But why would I keep myself
from laughing?

90
00:06:55,733 --> 00:07:00,567
If we can find a reason
to laugh, why deprive ourselves?

91
00:07:00,633 --> 00:07:03,100
Sorry, but your jokes
are not helping.

92
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:06,233
Stop being mean.

93
00:07:06,300 --> 00:07:08,900
I'm not being mean, Red!

94
00:07:08,967 --> 00:07:11,667
I want you to care the way I do.

95
00:07:13,833 --> 00:07:15,767
We're helpless!

96
00:07:15,867 --> 00:07:17,700
We're in the middle of nowhere.

97
00:07:19,100 --> 00:07:22,533
Come on! I don't know how
you can take this so lightly.

98
00:07:23,867 --> 00:07:26,100
I'm not treating
the situation lightly.

99
00:07:26,167 --> 00:07:27,467
I just wanted us to feel better.

100
00:07:27,533 --> 00:07:28,500
I was just trying...

101
00:07:30,467 --> 00:07:31,433
Never mind.

102
00:07:33,633 --> 00:07:35,300
Fine, I'm sorry.

103
00:07:35,367 --> 00:07:36,833
Sorry for upsetting you.

104
00:07:38,133 --> 00:07:40,500
But you don't have
the right to judge me

105
00:07:40,567 --> 00:07:43,067
just because I'm trying
to make things lighter.

106
00:07:44,667 --> 00:07:45,767
You don't know me.

107
00:07:47,067 --> 00:07:48,900
You don't know
what I'm going through.

108
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:50,833
You have no idea what my family
is going through.

109
00:08:38,967 --> 00:08:40,200
Son...

110
00:08:40,267 --> 00:08:41,267
Red...

111
00:08:47,633 --> 00:08:49,133
Your brother's gone.

112
00:08:50,233 --> 00:08:53,400
He won't be with us anymore.

113
00:08:54,567 --> 00:08:58,100
Mom, don't cry.

114
00:08:58,167 --> 00:08:59,333
I'm here for you.

115
00:09:00,367 --> 00:09:01,733
I know.

116
00:09:01,800 --> 00:09:06,733
But we're thinking
about your safety.

117
00:09:06,800 --> 00:09:13,600
That's why we've decided
to send you back to the States.

118
00:09:13,667 --> 00:09:14,633
But, Mom...

119
00:09:15,767 --> 00:09:17,433
Dad.

120
00:09:17,500 --> 00:09:18,700
I just got here.

121
00:09:20,067 --> 00:09:22,367
I didn't get a chance
to be with my brother.

122
00:09:24,200 --> 00:09:25,900
I just want to be with you now.

123
00:09:27,900 --> 00:09:29,633
Don't worry, Red.

124
00:09:29,700 --> 00:09:32,533
We'll visit you often.

125
00:09:32,600 --> 00:09:34,333
Why not come with me then?

126
00:09:35,600 --> 00:09:36,700
Come here.

127
00:09:41,833 --> 00:09:45,867
We still have a lot
to take care of.

128
00:09:48,233 --> 00:09:52,200
Whoever killed your brother
has to pay.

129
00:09:53,933 --> 00:09:57,200
And we will never stop
until justice is served.

130
00:10:00,267 --> 00:10:02,433
Your mom will be happy
to see you.

131
00:10:04,633 --> 00:10:06,933
Look at her. That's what
she does every day.

132
00:10:14,600 --> 00:10:15,567
Mom...

133
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:18,067
I'm back!

134
00:10:19,433 --> 00:10:20,667
My son!

135
00:10:25,133 --> 00:10:27,400
You're home!

136
00:10:28,400 --> 00:10:29,567
- How are you?
- This is enough.

137
00:10:29,633 --> 00:10:30,767
- I'm okay. How was...
- No more drinking for you.

138
00:10:30,833 --> 00:10:32,300
Hey!

139
00:10:32,367 --> 00:10:34,233
Mom, you're drunk.

140
00:10:34,300 --> 00:10:35,567
How was your trip?

141
00:10:36,900 --> 00:10:37,900
I'm good, I'm good.

142
00:10:37,967 --> 00:10:39,233
- That's good.
- I didn't know

143
00:10:39,300 --> 00:10:40,700
you were drinking.

144
00:10:43,667 --> 00:10:46,067
Mom, I'm staying for good.

145
00:10:47,100 --> 00:10:48,767
I'm not leaving you again.

146
00:10:48,833 --> 00:10:50,500
I'm going to continue
my studies here.

147
00:10:56,667 --> 00:10:57,700
Are you sure?

148
00:10:58,733 --> 00:11:00,300
Yeah.

149
00:11:00,367 --> 00:11:01,267
A hundred percent.

150
00:11:01,333 --> 00:11:02,800
I'll take care of you.

151
00:11:02,867 --> 00:11:04,333
I'm staying here.
I'm not going anywhere.

152
00:11:05,800 --> 00:11:06,800
Why?

153
00:11:07,967 --> 00:11:10,167
Am I sick?

154
00:11:11,167 --> 00:11:16,533
And you'll be better off
in the States.

155
00:11:16,600 --> 00:11:17,567
No.

156
00:11:18,733 --> 00:11:21,367
I'll stay here
with you and dad, okay?

157
00:11:23,300 --> 00:11:26,033
You're so stubborn.

158
00:11:26,100 --> 00:11:27,500
Of course, where do you think
I get it from?

159
00:11:27,567 --> 00:11:28,733
I take got it from you!

160
00:11:31,167 --> 00:11:33,600
You haven't changed a bit.

161
00:11:33,667 --> 00:11:34,933
You're still naughty.

162
00:11:35,933 --> 00:11:37,300
I missed hearing you laugh, Mom.

163
00:11:38,400 --> 00:11:40,133
You know, Mom...

164
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:44,033
Now that I'm back, every day I'm
going to make you laugh.

165
00:11:44,133 --> 00:11:46,033
I'm going to make you happy.

166
00:11:46,100 --> 00:11:49,400
So you won't need to drink
anymore just to be happy.

167
00:11:51,667 --> 00:11:52,900
I missed you, Son.

168
00:11:54,500 --> 00:11:55,667
I missed you so much.

169
00:12:21,667 --> 00:12:23,200
Red?

170
00:12:23,267 --> 00:12:24,233
Are you okay now?

171
00:12:28,200 --> 00:12:29,167
Yeah, I'm good.

172
00:12:33,500 --> 00:12:34,500
Sorry about earlier.

173
00:12:34,567 --> 00:12:36,867
I overreacted.

174
00:12:36,933 --> 00:12:39,433
I'm the one
who should apologize.

175
00:12:39,500 --> 00:12:41,000
I shouldn't have judged you.

176
00:12:42,300 --> 00:12:43,500
It's over.

177
00:12:43,567 --> 00:12:44,900
Let's just move forward.

178
00:12:44,967 --> 00:12:48,667
Okay. So I did an inventory
earlier.

179
00:12:49,900 --> 00:12:51,833
Aside from rope and flashlight,

180
00:12:51,900 --> 00:12:54,600
I found something else
we could use.

181
00:12:54,667 --> 00:12:55,700
Do you want to see it?

182
00:12:55,767 --> 00:12:56,667
- Yes, let's go.
- Come on.

183
00:12:56,733 --> 00:12:57,700
Come on.

184
00:13:03,667 --> 00:13:04,733
It was wrapped in a towel.

185
00:13:04,800 --> 00:13:06,333
That's why we didn't see it.

186
00:13:09,467 --> 00:13:10,400
Biscuits.

187
00:13:14,667 --> 00:13:16,167
We have something to eat now.

188
00:13:17,167 --> 00:13:18,400
Right.

189
00:13:18,467 --> 00:13:21,167
But I found something else.

190
00:13:22,233 --> 00:13:24,167
I don't know if we can use this.

191
00:13:25,467 --> 00:13:26,500
Do you drink?

192
00:13:30,500 --> 00:13:31,800
I know someone who does.

193
00:13:33,933 --> 00:13:36,800
Okay, I'll keep it
for whatever purpose.

194
00:13:36,867 --> 00:13:39,367
We might need it
sooner or later.

195
00:13:41,467 --> 00:13:44,533
It's good that we have something
to eat and drink now.

196
00:13:44,600 --> 00:13:48,200
Right. But this is not enough.

197
00:13:48,267 --> 00:13:49,900
We need to find some more stuff.

198
00:13:49,967 --> 00:13:52,967
I'm confident that rescuers
will be here anytime soon.

199
00:13:54,100 --> 00:13:58,167
Yeah, but we don't know
when will they be here.

200
00:13:58,267 --> 00:14:02,733
So we still need to find
food, water, and shelter.

201
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:07,333
We can only do that
if we help each other.

202
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:13,333
Okay.

203
00:14:13,400 --> 00:14:15,967
We'll help each other
from now on.

204
00:14:16,033 --> 00:14:18,300
To get things done.

205
00:14:20,633 --> 00:14:21,433
Deal.

206
00:15:06,067 --> 00:15:07,033
Red!

207
00:15:08,933 --> 00:15:10,533
It will be dark soon.

208
00:15:10,600 --> 00:15:12,100
Don't waste the batteries.

209
00:15:12,167 --> 00:15:13,733
We will need that later.

210
00:15:13,800 --> 00:15:15,433
A boat might pass by.

211
00:15:15,500 --> 00:15:17,067
They will see my signal.

212
00:15:18,967 --> 00:15:20,267
How's the fire going?

213
00:15:21,300 --> 00:15:23,100
The wood is still damp.

214
00:15:23,167 --> 00:15:26,333
It's hard to fire it up,
but I have to try.

215
00:15:27,867 --> 00:15:29,433
Try and try until you succeed!

216
00:15:31,567 --> 00:15:33,467
Are you already tired?
Do you want me to do it?

217
00:15:33,533 --> 00:15:34,933
No, I'm okay.

218
00:15:51,133 --> 00:15:53,133
Dindi. Dindi,
what's the emergency?

219
00:15:53,200 --> 00:15:55,100
Why are you here?

220
00:15:55,167 --> 00:15:57,133
Amanda, I found out about it
last night.

221
00:15:57,200 --> 00:15:59,867
But I had to confirm it first.

222
00:15:59,933 --> 00:16:01,900
That's why it took me a while
to come here.

223
00:16:03,333 --> 00:16:05,900
How should I tell you this?

224
00:16:05,967 --> 00:16:08,500
Dindi, what's going on?

225
00:16:08,600 --> 00:16:11,133
Is this about Yenyen?

226
00:16:11,200 --> 00:16:12,667
Is she back?

227
00:16:12,733 --> 00:16:14,933
Yenyen is not back yet.

228
00:16:16,767 --> 00:16:17,933
What happened?

229
00:16:18,967 --> 00:16:25,067
Her plane back to Manila
is missing.

230
00:16:25,133 --> 00:16:26,933
They said it might have crashed.

231
00:16:31,933 --> 00:16:33,300
Amanda.

232
00:16:37,300 --> 00:16:38,300
That's not true.

233
00:16:38,367 --> 00:16:39,733
- But they said that...
- That's not true!

234
00:16:39,800 --> 00:16:40,900
- That's not true.
- They said there might be

235
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:42,033
survivors, Amanda.

236
00:16:44,833 --> 00:16:46,167
I'm sorry, Amanda.

237
00:16:47,867 --> 00:16:49,000
That's not true.

238
00:16:52,633 --> 00:16:53,767
Amanda.

239
00:16:59,867 --> 00:17:03,033
Didn't we suffer enough?

240
00:17:04,500 --> 00:17:06,467
Why did this have to happen?

241
00:17:07,500 --> 00:17:09,467
Amanda, don't lose hope.

242
00:17:09,533 --> 00:17:11,667
They said they might be
survivors.

243
00:17:11,733 --> 00:17:13,133
They might find Yenyen.

244
00:17:13,200 --> 00:17:14,833
Right?

245
00:17:14,900 --> 00:17:16,167
I don't know, Dindi.

246
00:17:17,900 --> 00:17:19,400
I'm so tired.

247
00:17:21,667 --> 00:17:23,900
Nothing good ever happens
to my life.

248
00:17:23,967 --> 00:17:25,400
What did I do wrong?

249
00:17:25,467 --> 00:17:27,833
Why are we being punished
like this?

250
00:17:33,167 --> 00:17:36,233
Amanda, don't lose hope.

251
00:17:36,300 --> 00:17:37,600
Don't think like that.

252
00:17:37,667 --> 00:17:38,833
We have to be strong.

253
00:17:40,433 --> 00:17:42,100
We'll find her.

254
00:17:45,433 --> 00:17:46,400
Amanda.

255
00:18:02,267 --> 00:18:03,233
Crackers?

256
00:18:05,100 --> 00:18:06,667
Let's share this, okay?

257
00:18:06,733 --> 00:18:08,567
We have to ration our food.

258
00:18:08,633 --> 00:18:09,633
I'm okay.

259
00:18:09,700 --> 00:18:11,600
I'm not hungry.

260
00:18:11,667 --> 00:18:12,633
Come on.

261
00:18:12,700 --> 00:18:13,800
You need nourishment.

262
00:18:14,833 --> 00:18:16,800
We have a lot to do tomorrow.

263
00:18:22,267 --> 00:18:23,333
What's so funny?

264
00:18:24,433 --> 00:18:28,700
You care like a mother.

265
00:18:28,767 --> 00:18:30,133
I don't mean it the wrong way.

266
00:18:32,300 --> 00:18:33,467
It's okay.

267
00:18:33,533 --> 00:18:34,567
I know what I'm like.

268
00:18:36,533 --> 00:18:41,067
I matured pretty early
for having a hard-knock life.

269
00:18:59,800 --> 00:19:01,100
Here, have some crackers.

270
00:19:05,267 --> 00:19:06,233
Okay.

271
00:19:20,467 --> 00:19:21,500
We'll split this in half.

272
00:19:22,833 --> 00:19:24,067
Okay, ladies first.

273
00:19:36,167 --> 00:19:38,000
Let's save this for tomorrow.

274
00:19:41,900 --> 00:19:43,333
Get some rest.

275
00:19:43,400 --> 00:19:44,900
I'll take care of everything.

276
00:19:44,967 --> 00:19:47,100
I'll stay for a while.
A boat might pass by.

277
00:19:51,400 --> 00:19:52,867
Don't be sacred.

278
00:19:52,933 --> 00:19:54,700
I'll be right here.

279
00:19:54,767 --> 00:19:56,767
I'm not just scared, Red.

280
00:19:56,833 --> 00:19:59,033
I'm also worried about my mom.

281
00:20:02,300 --> 00:20:05,700
By now, I'm sure she heard
about what happened.

282
00:20:09,367 --> 00:20:12,200
I don't know
how she can take this news.

283
00:20:17,967 --> 00:20:18,933
Okay.

284
00:20:20,667 --> 00:20:21,800
I'm going to get some rest.

285
00:20:47,467 --> 00:20:49,333
Amanda Sta. Maria,

286
00:20:49,400 --> 00:20:52,667
guilty beyond reasonable doubt
as accomplice

287
00:20:52,733 --> 00:20:55,067
to the crime of robbery
with homicide

288
00:20:55,133 --> 00:20:58,667
as defined and penalized
under the revised penal code.

289
00:21:00,367 --> 00:21:01,400
Let's go! We have to go home.

290
00:21:01,467 --> 00:21:03,033
Come on! Let's go home!

291
00:21:06,200 --> 00:21:08,300
I'll stay here!

292
00:21:09,400 --> 00:21:10,367
Mom!

293
00:21:13,300 --> 00:21:14,300
Yen.

294
00:21:23,067 --> 00:21:24,700
Yen, what happened?

295
00:21:25,900 --> 00:21:27,900
You were having a nightmare.

296
00:21:27,967 --> 00:21:29,567
I had a dream about my mom.

297
00:21:31,467 --> 00:21:32,933
Why?

298
00:21:33,000 --> 00:21:34,333
What happened?

299
00:21:36,233 --> 00:21:37,833
We got separated.

300
00:21:40,100 --> 00:21:41,067
She was jailed.

301
00:21:43,533 --> 00:21:44,500
What?

302
00:21:46,033 --> 00:21:48,000
Someone cruel had her
put in jail.

303
00:21:53,400 --> 00:21:54,367
God...

304
00:22:00,300 --> 00:22:05,400
I don't know why you let this
happen to us.

305
00:22:07,167 --> 00:22:10,100
But I believe that you have
a reason for all of this.

306
00:22:13,833 --> 00:22:19,000
How can I be free
without my daughter?

307
00:22:27,233 --> 00:22:31,133
I don't understand
what you want from us.

308
00:22:34,767 --> 00:22:37,767
But I believe
that you have a reason.

309
00:22:42,933 --> 00:22:44,900
And whatever reason you have...

310
00:22:48,567 --> 00:22:50,800
that is what's best for us.

311
00:23:02,833 --> 00:23:04,533
Why?

312
00:23:04,600 --> 00:23:07,233
What happened? What did she do?

313
00:23:07,300 --> 00:23:09,033
She didn't do anything wrong.

314
00:23:09,100 --> 00:23:10,433
She was just accused.

315
00:23:11,500 --> 00:23:16,433
The family who accused her
is influential.

316
00:23:18,533 --> 00:23:19,433
Tell me.

317
00:23:19,500 --> 00:23:20,900
Tell me what happened.

318
00:23:22,567 --> 00:23:23,600
Sorry, Red.

319
00:23:25,100 --> 00:23:26,533
I don't want
to talk about it now.

320
00:23:29,100 --> 00:23:30,500
Just leave me alone.

321
00:23:33,033 --> 00:23:33,900
Yen.

322
00:23:41,133 --> 00:23:42,333
Dindi, any news?

323
00:23:44,067 --> 00:23:47,800
There's still no news
about where the plane crashed.

324
00:23:50,667 --> 00:23:52,600
Are they still going to find
my daughter?

325
00:23:53,733 --> 00:23:55,367
Amanda, God has mercy.

326
00:23:56,633 --> 00:23:58,633
It's all the Ramoses' fault.

327
00:23:58,700 --> 00:24:02,167
If they didn't accuse me,
I wouldn't be in jail.

328
00:24:02,233 --> 00:24:04,100
I wouldn't be separated
from my daughter.

329
00:24:05,900 --> 00:24:07,200
It's all their fault.

330
00:24:07,267 --> 00:24:09,200
If something bad happens
to my daughter,

331
00:24:09,267 --> 00:24:11,300
I will make them pay!

332
00:24:36,300 --> 00:24:37,233
Red?

333
00:25:00,767 --> 00:25:04,967
Can you do something
to expedite my release papers?

334
00:25:05,067 --> 00:25:09,200
The plane that my daughter
boarded crashed.

335
00:25:09,267 --> 00:25:12,900
I want to do something
to find her.

336
00:25:12,967 --> 00:25:15,933
I'm sorry about what happened
to your daughter, Amanda.

337
00:25:16,000 --> 00:25:20,133
But I don't think I can do
something about your request.

338
00:25:20,200 --> 00:25:22,700
Did you know that she's getting
released from prison?

339
00:25:22,767 --> 00:25:24,167
How is that possible?

340
00:25:24,233 --> 00:25:27,000
I want to get even with her
before she gets released.

341
00:25:27,067 --> 00:25:28,533
What do you want to do?

342
00:25:31,767 --> 00:25:33,300
Yen, let's follow the sound.

343
00:25:33,367 --> 00:25:35,267
- Come on!
- Help.
